Day 5: SQL – DDL (CREATE / ALTER / DROP)

Topic:
SQL Data Definition Language (DDL)

Learning Objectives:

Understand DDL commands used to define and manage database structures
Learn how to create, alter, and delete databases and tables
Understand different data types in SQL
Learn constraints such as NOT NULL, UNIQUE, and DEFAULT

Activities / Deliverables:

Create a database named VolyoDB
Build 5 tables using different SQL data types
Apply constraints like NOT NULL, UNIQUE, and DEFAULT
Practice CREATE, ALTER, and DROP commands
Test table modifications and schema updates using SQL queries

Tools / Tech:

MySQL 8
MySQL Command Line Interface (CLI)

